[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m - \( y \) = number of days Jenna trains for three hours
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m I understand that Jenna has a seven-day week, so the total number of days is 7. This gives me one equation:
