[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m \]
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m So now I have a quadratic equation: \(10x^2 - 14x - 7 = 0\).
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m To determine the nature of the solutions (and therefore the relationship between the line and the circle), I need to find the discriminant of this quadratic equation. The discriminant, \(D\), is given by \(D = b^2 - 4ac\), where \(a = 10\), \(b = -14\), and \(c = -7\).
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m Calculating the discriminant:
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m \[
