[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m So, the discriminant is 476, which is positive. A positive discriminant indicates that there are two distinct real solutions, which means the line intersects the circle at two distinct points. Therefore, the line is secant to the circle.
