[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m * consider visiting your local animal poison control center as many states have established telephone numbers for such emergencies these specialists can provide immediate advice on the treatment options for your dog based on rat poison ingestion they may recommend toxicology testing and medication management plans that could potentially be covered by your pet insurance if available
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m * if over the next few days your dog shows severe symptoms such as lethargyCallback pain weakness or breathing difficulties you should seek prompt veterinary care as the situation can become life threatening without proper medical intervention be prepared with details of the incident including how the poison was administered what you believe to be the exact product dosage and any other information that might help the medical professionals evaluate the situation
