[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m First, I need to calculate the variance for Dataset A: {12, 15, 18, 21, 24} and Dataset B: {30, 27, 33, 36, 39}.
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m For variance calculation:
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 1. Calculate the mean of each dataset.
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 2. Subtract the mean from each value and square the result.
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 3. Find the average of those squared differences.
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m For Dataset A:
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m Mean = (12 + 15 + 18 + 21 + 24)/5 = 84/5 = 16.8
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m Differences: (12-16.8)¬≤ = 21.16, (15-16.8)¬≤ = 3.24, (18-16.8)¬≤ = 1.44, (21-16.8)¬≤ = 17.64, (24-16.8)¬≤ = 74.56
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m Variance = (21.16 + 3.24 + 1.44 + 17.64 + 74.56)/5 = 118.44/5 = 23.69
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m For Dataset B:
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m Mean = (30 + 27 + 33 + 36 + 39)/5 = 155/5 = 31
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m Differences: (30-31)¬≤ = 1, (27-31)¬≤ = 16, (33-31)¬≤ = 4, (36-31)¬≤ = 25, (39-31)¬≤ = 64
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m Variance = (1 + 16 + 4 + 25 + 64)/5 = 100/5 = 20
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m So, Dataset A has a variance of 23.69, Dataset B has a variance of 20. The standard deviation for Dataset A is sqrt(23.69) ‚âà 4.87 and for Dataset B it's sqrt(20) ‚âà 4.47.
