[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m First off, I need to recall what a cube is. A cube is a three-dimensional shape with all sides equal and all angles right angles. Each face of a cube is a square, and since a cube has six faces, the total surface area can be calculated by finding the area of one face and then multiplying by 6.
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
