[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m Now, the main task is to find the distance between the midpoints of two skew edges of the cube. Let me think about what skew edges are. In a cube, skew edges are edges that neither intersect nor are parallel. They exist in different planes and don't intersect even when extended infinitely in both directions.
