[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m Raymond III Count of Tripoli was born in 1267 in the County of Tripoli which is present-day Lebanon. He was a prominent noble and played a significant role in the history of the Kingdom of Jerusalem. Raymond III inherited the County of Tripoli at a young age and became known for his military prowess and political acumen.
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m *Raymond III's military career was marked by his participation in several key conflicts including the Second and Third Crusades* where he fought against both the Saladin and the Mongols. He was a trusted advisor to King Henry II of France and served as a representative for the County of Tripoli in the Holy Land. Raymond III was known for his Christian faith and his support for Christian crusaders during the conflicts with the Mongols.
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m *His most famous action occurred during the Battle of le grand plain where his forces defeated a Mongol army*. Raymond III demonstrated exceptional leadership during this battle which solidified his reputation as a valiant warrior. After the death of King Henry II in 1287 Raymond III inherited the French throne making him one of the few French kings who served as a military commander in the Crusades.
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m Raymond III spent the latter part of his life in France where he continued to support the Christian crusaders. *His death in 1325 occurred while fleeing from Mongol forces after the fall of Constantinople* according to some accounts. Raymond III's legacy includes his contributions to the defense of Christian interests in the Holy Land and his political influence in both the County of Tripoli and the County of France.
