[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m I remember that the absolute value of a number is its distance from zero on the number line, regardless of direction. So, if \( a \) is negative, \( |a| \) would be its positive counterpart. For example, if \( a = -5 \), then \( |a| = 5 \).
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
