[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m Since \( a \) is negative, \( |a| = -a \) (because multiplying by -1 gives the positive version). Therefore, dividing \( a \) by \( |a| \) would be \( a / (-a) \), which simplifies to -1.
