[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m Let me denote:
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m - Point E on AB: Since AB goes from (0,0) to (s,0), point E must be at (e,0) where 0 ‚â§ e ‚â§ s.
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m - Point Z on CD: Since CD goes from (s,s) to (0,s), point Z must be at (z,s) where 0 ‚â§ z ‚â§ s.
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m Now, it's given that DE is parallel to BZ. That is, the line segment DE is parallel to segment BZ.
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m Let me find the slopes of DE and BZ to establish this parallelism.
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m Coordinates:
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m - D is at (0,s)
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m - E is at (e,0)
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m - B is at (s,0)
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m - Z is at (z,s)
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m Slope of DE:
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m m_DE = (0 - s)/(e - 0) = (-s)/e
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m Slope of BZ:
