[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m Points of the parallelogram:
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m - B: (s,0)
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m - E: (e,0)
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m - D: (0,s)
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m - Z: (z,s)
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m We can also compute the area using vectors or the shoelace formula.
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m But since DE and BZ are parallel, and BEDZ is a parallelogram, the area can be computed as |(vector BE) √ó (vector BZ)|
