[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m Hence, area of BEDZ is s(s - e)
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m But the problem states that the areas of triangles EAD, ZCB, and the parallelogram are all equal.
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m So:
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m Area(EAD) = Area(ZCB) = Area(BEDZ)
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m From above:
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m (1/2)es = (1/2)es = s(s - e)
