[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 2. Since $DE \parallel BZ$, their slopes are equal:
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m    - Slope of $DE$ is $\frac{-s}{e}$
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m    - Slope of $BZ$ is $\frac{s}{z - s}$
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m    - Equating slopes: $\frac{-s}{e} = \frac{s}{z - s}$ leads to $z = s - e$.
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 3. Calculate areas:
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m    - Area of $\triangle EAD$ is $\frac{1}{2}es$
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m    - Area of $\triangle ZCB$ is $\frac{1}{2}es$
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m    - Area of parallelogram $BEDZ$ is $s(s - e)$
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m 4. Set areas equal:
[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m    - $\frac{1}{2}es = s(s - e)$
