[36m(main_task pid=25448)[0m The molecular weight (molar mass) of NaCl is important here. Sodium (Na) has an atomic weight of approximately 23 g/mol, and chlorine (Cl) has an atomic weight of approximately 35 g/mol. So the molar mass of NaCl is about 23 + 35 = 58 g/mol.
